theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  -- Set an abbreviation for readability.
  set s : Set X := interior A with hs
  -- We establish the two inclusions separately.
  have h₁ : closure s ⊆ closure (interior (closure s)) := by
    -- It suffices to show `s ⊆ interior (closure s)`.
    have hSub : s ⊆ interior (closure s) := by
      -- `s` is open and contained in its closure.
      have hSub' : s ⊆ closure s := by
        intro x hx; exact subset_closure hx
      have hOpen : IsOpen s := by
        simpa [hs] using isOpen_interior
      exact interior_maximal hSub' hOpen
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    exact closure_mono hSub
  have h₂ : closure (interior (closure s)) ⊆ closure s := by
    -- `interior (closure s)` is contained in `closure s`.
    have hSub : interior (closure s) ⊆ closure s := interior_subset
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    exact closure_mono hSub
  -- Combine the two inclusions to get equality.
  have hEq : closure (interior (closure s)) = closure s :=
    Set.Subset.antisymm h₂ h₁
  -- Revert the abbreviation and finish.
  simpa [hs] using hEq
